article.headline: Smith's 19 help Radford defeat Presbyterian 73-58
article.description: — DaQuan Smith had 19 points in Radford's 73-58 win against Presbyterian on Saturday night.
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- — DaQuan Smith had 19 points in Radford's 73-58 win against Presbyterian on Saturday night. Smith was 7-of-14 shooting (5 for 10 from 3-point range) for the Highlanders (13-9, 3-4 Big South Conference). Kenyon Giles scored 17 points and added six rebounds. Bryan Antoine shot 5 for 11, including 3 for 7 from beyond the arc to finish with 13 points. The Blue Hose (9-13, 1-6) were led by Samage Teel, who recorded 17 points. Trevon Reddish added 13 points for Presbyterian. Marquis Barnett also put up nine points. The Blue Hose extended their losing streak to six straight. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
